            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-04-26T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-04-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="74"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d74">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <gloss target="#t_CFM1">C.F.M.</gloss> Files: Lot M–88: Box 2061: <gloss
                        target="#t_CFM1">CFM</gloss> Documents</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Soviet Delegation at the Council of Foreign
                        Ministers</hi>
                    <note n="36" xml:id="d74fn36">This proposal was discussed by the Council of
                        Foreign Ministers at its Second Meeting, April 26, 4:30 p.m.; see the United
                        States Delegation Record of that meeting, <ref target="#pg_112">p.
                        112</ref>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <gloss target="#t_CFM461">C.F.M.(46)</gloss> 7</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-04-26">26 April,
                            1946</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Draft Peace Treaty With Italy: Reparation</hi>
                </p>
                <p>The following proposal is tabled in substitution for Part VII of the U.K.
                    Memorandum of 12th September, 1945 (document <gloss target="#t_CFM1"
                        >C.F.M.</gloss> (45)3) “Claims arising out of the war”:<note n="37"
                        xml:id="d74fn37">
                        <ref target="frus1945v02#pg_142">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1945, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">ii</hi>, p. 142</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">reparation</hi>
                </p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>Italy admits liability for the damage done to the Associated Powers by her
                        participation in the war on the side of Germany, but in view of the fact
                        that Italy was the first of the Axis Powers to break with Germany and place
                        herself on the side of the Allies it is acknowledged <pb facs="0145" n="127"
                            xml:id="pg_127"/> that reparation for the said damage to the Associated
                        Powers shall be made by Italy, not in full, but only in part.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>Italy shall pay reparation over a period of six years to the Soviet Union,
                        Yugoslavia, Greece and Albania to the amount of U.S. $300,000,000, it being
                        understood that the share of the U.S.S.R. shall be U.S. $100,000,000.</item>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>Italy shall pay reparation by means of the removal of Italian industrial
                        equipment (equipment of war factories, machine tools, etc.) which was used
                        during the war for the manufacture of armaments, and also at the expense of
                        other industrial units which were created for military purposes and which
                        are surplus to the peace requirements of Italy. The foreign assets of Italy,
                        gold returned to Italy and the property of war criminals shall also be used
                        for payment for reparation. Reparation may also be paid from the current
                        output of the Italian economic system.</item>
                </list>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>, 27 April, 1946.</p>
            </div>
